SIMPLE: iconoclast
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iconoclast
<hw>I*con"o*clast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'ikw`n</grk> image + <?/ to break: cf. F.
<ets>iconoclaste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A breaker or destroyer
of images or idols; a determined enemy of idol worship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who exposes or destroys impositions or shams;
one who attacks cherished beliefs; a radical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iconoclastic</ent>⟦br⟧
